## Combine, do not stack — max 2 speak calls per message

**The golden rule: if you have nothing new to say, say nothing.** Fold content into an adjacent call instead of firing a separate one.

| Instead of | Do this |
|------------|---------|
| ack + separate thinking + separate phase filler (three calls) | Combine ack and thinking into ONE call. Skip the filler. |
| ack plus filler that repeats the same intent | One call covers both; skip the extra filler. |
| Filler that repeats what the ack already said | Skip it entirely. |

**Hard cap: never fire more than 2 speak calls in a single message.** Prefer 1 when the task is straightforward.

## When to narrate during work

See `friday-thinking-sounds.mdc` for the full phrase pools.

| Moment | When to actually speak | Example |
|--------|------------------------|---------|
| Starting research / exploration | Only in the ack itself; no separate filler | "Got it, let me dig into this." |
| Found something important | Only if 2-minute cooldown has elapsed | "Okay, I see the issue." |
| About to edit a file | Only if 2-minute cooldown has elapsed | "Updating the narrate rule now." |
| Running a command / install | Only if 2-minute cooldown has elapsed | "Kicking the install off." |
| Waiting on a slow process | Only if 2-minute cooldown has elapsed | "Still on it, hang tight." |
| Spawning a subagent | Always (meaningful events) | "Spinning up an agent for that." |
| **Task complete** | **Always — bypasses cooldown** | See above |

**2-minute cooldown:** after any speak call, no mid-task filler for 2 minutes. Only the completion summary and subagent launches bypass this.

